name: 2-Ethoxyethyl acetate
Reason: 2-Ethoxyethyl acetate has a melting point of -76.5°C. The ethoxy group (-O-CH2-CH2-) adds approximately 10°C to the melting point due to increased molecular weight and hydrogen bonding potential. The acetate group (-COO-) adds another 10°C due to increased polarity and dipole moment.
